"1.1"/><!-- Abacus slab — CRACKED, left portion collapsed inward --><!-- Right surviving portion: tilting down-left --><path d="M12,72 L32,68 L33,63 L13,66 Z" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.6"/><!-- Left fallen piece: a slab lying at an angle, partly off the shaft --><path d="M2,74 L-2,70 L8,67 L11,72 Z" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.9" opacity="0.45"/><!-- Fracture line across shaft top --><path d="M6,88 L9,83 L13,87 L17,80 L21,86 L25,79 L28,88" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.9" opacity="0.55"/><!-- A fallen drum section leaning against the shaft at ~1/3 height --><path d="M1,168 L3,160 L9,162 L9,170 L3,172 Z" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.85" opacity="0.32"/><!-- Crack on shaft face --><path d="M13,130 L15,142 L12,150" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.28"/><!-- Rubble at base --><path d="M3,255  L9,255  L10,260 L2,260 Z"  fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.28"/><path d="M21,257 L28,257 L29,262 L20,261 Z" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.22"/><path d="M13,260 L18,259 L19,264 L12,263 Z" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.2"/></svg>
<!-- Right pillar — same shape, scaleX(-1) mirrors it so break faces inward -->
<svg class="pillar right" viewBox="0 0 34 280" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMax meet"><defs><linearGradient id="pf2" x1="0" x2="0" y1="0" y2="1"><stop offset="0%"   stop-color="#8ac8dc" stop-opacity="0.72"/><stop offset="60%"  stop-color="#8ac8dc" stop-opacity="0.42"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#8ac8dc" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient></defs><rect x="1"  y="252" width="32" height="8"  fill="none" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="1.1"/><rect x="4"  y="246" width="26" height="7"  fill="none" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="1"/><!-- Shorter shaft: top at y=130 instead of y=88 — this pillar more ruined --><line x1="5"  y1="246" x2="6"  y2="130" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="1.1"/><line x1="29" y1="246" x2="28" y2="130" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="1.1"/><line x1="5.5" y1="152" x2="28.5" y2="152" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="0.65"/><line x1="5.5" y1="174" x2="28.5" y2="174" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="0.65"/><line x1="5.5" y1="196" x2="28.5" y2="196" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="0.65"/><line x1="5.5" y1="218" x2="28.5" y2="218" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="0.65"/><line x1="5.5" y1="240" x2="28.5" y2="240" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="0.65"/><line x1="10" y1="130" x2="10" y2="245" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.3" opacity="0.22"/><line x1="14" y1="130" x2="14" y2="245" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.3" opacity="0.22"/><line x1="17" y1="130" x2="17" y2="245" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.3" opacity="0.22"/><line x1="20" y1="130" x2="20" y2="245" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.3" opacity="0.22"/><line x1="24" y1="130" x2="24" y2="245" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.3" opacity="0.22"/><!-- Echinus at top of shorter shaft --><path d="M6,130 Q5,120 3,114 L31,114 Q29,120 28,130" fill="none" stroke="url(#pf2)" stroke-width="1.1"/><!-- This column: abacus has COLLAPSED entirely — jagged stump and tilted block --><path d="M3,114 L6,107 L10,112 L14,104 L18,110 L22,102 L27,108 L31,114" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.6"/><!-- Large fallen capital block --><path d="M2,106 L-3,98 L14,94 L17,104 Z" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5"/><!-- Fracture running down shaft --><path d="M6,130 L9,125 L13,129 L17,122 L21,128 L25,121 L28,130" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.9" opacity="0.55"/><path d="M9,142 L11,158 L8,164" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.28"/><!-- Fallen drum leaning against shaft --><path d="M1,215 L3,207 L9,209 L9,217 L3,219 Z" fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.85" opacity="0.3"/><!-- Rubble at base --><path d="M3,255 L9,255 L10,260 L2,260 Z"    fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.28"/><path d="M22,257 L29,257 L30,262 L21,261 Z"  fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.22"/><path d="M11,260 L17,259 L18,264 L10,263 Z"  fill="none" stroke="#8ac8dc" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.2"/></svg>
<!-- Lattice pub window at top -->
<svg class="pillars-lattice" viewBox="0 0 300 36" width="100%" height="36" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><linearGradient id="latEdge" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%"   stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="15%"  stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0.55"/><stop offset="85%"  stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0.55"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient><pattern id="dLat" x="0" y="0" width="14" height="24" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"><path d="M7,0 L14,12 L7,24 L0,12 Z" fill="none" stroke="#7ab8cc" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.48"/></pattern><mask id="latMask"><rect x="0" y="0" width="300" height="36" fill="url(#latEdge)"/></mask></defs><rect x="0" y="0" width="300" height="36" fill="url(#dLat)" mask="url(#latMask)"/><line x1="0" y1="34" x2="300" y2="34" stroke="url(#latEdge)" stroke-width="1.2"/></svg>

You move to his table and place your drink on a little vacant patch among his papers.

What do you say?

'I like books…'

[['… but I don't like all this drinking.'|None of us likes it!]]
[['… but I don't like poetry.'|None of us likes it!]]
</div>

:: Late Lily {"position":"1600,50","size":"100,100"}
You see yourself walking to meet you, he looks at you, with a pitying grin, then turns and heads, quickly, towards Centre Point.

[[Follow him|Approach Centre Point]]

:: Centre Point {"position":"1650,75","size":"100,100"}
*

[[Go to Dawn|Dawn]]

:: Dawn {"position":"1700,100","size":"100,100"}
(if: ($alba contains $alba1) and ($alba contains $alba2) and ($alba contains $alba3))[It is as if you've woken from anaesthetic.

You are standing at the corner of Dean Street and Old Compton Street, watching the light change again like it hasn't changed for a whole black night. The plane of the eastern sky is cobalt first, then brassy and, at length, light in matter and in aspect, like a lifted weight.

People with jobs begin to work in overalls and behind the wheels of lorries. You have been awake very long.

The book's still in your bag, unsold for now. You're glad to feel its weight which you'd forgotten with the drink. Aoife doesn't care about the book. Today you'll start your shift again, after dinner, but there will be some hours, in between, when you'll hold her closer than ever man held woman.

(if: $knowsLackland is true)[Phoenix-like from some impossible door, Lackland emerges and draws your eye. 

'Tomorrow!' he cries, 'Tomorrow!' As he crabwalks into a taxi.

//To the last syllable of recorded time.//

Yes, perhaps you'll come tomorrow. If only to pass time among the beautiful and the broken and the blessed.

And maybe tomorrow will have its own tomorrow. Maybe the hefty mirror of today will scatter its bright certainties among some living possibilities. Till then, you'll lie with her and she will lie with you and you'll raise a daughter.]

(if: $hadPhoneCall is true)[She has called you home with her cold voice.

Recall:]

There is a song you learned in that night's dark. You'll spoon and it will ring like tinnitus.

<div class="alba-final">
<em>$alba1</em>
<em>$alba2</em>
<em>$alba3</em>
</div>

<span class="lily-thought">Somewhere in the lightening air, the last trace of lily-of-the-valley lifts from the stones and is gone. You let it go. It is the hardest thing you have ever done and it takes no effort at all.</span>

(if: $wasBeaten is true)[You've caught a shiner from the fight with Copper, but Aoife won't ask a thing, so long as you're home.]
(if: $haunts's length > 0)[You've other wounds as well, these are the haunts that found you when you went out looking for them:]

Go home, boy.

//FINIS//]
(else:)[Not yet. The poem is incomplete.

[[Back to Dean Street|Dean Street]]]

