<div class="first-visit-hint">THE YORK MINSTER, KNOWN AS 'THE FRENCH'. TALK TO PEOPLE AND DRINK.</div>]
|lily5>[<div class="lily-prompt" style="display:inline-block; border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); border-radius:50%; width:2.5em; height:2.5em; line-height:2.5em; text-align:center; cursor:pointer;">⚘</div>]\
(click-replace: ?lily5)[(set: $lilyCount to $lilyCount + 1)<span class="lily-glimpse lily-fade">Was that her passing the window, almost six-foot and with the gait of a newborn antelope?</span>]

As you walk in the bar drops down to silence, as if its speech were interrupted by a quick gasp for breath, the way an antelope sometimes mistakes the wind in the grass for a lion, stiffens, then goes about its day.

At one end of the bar are the artists; you know them, they are famous.

Stuffed into a barstool which his arsecheeks overhang, like clouds waiting to rain, is a stout man with his back to you. His leather jacket, somehow both parched and sweating, falls short at the neck, flashing a collar of labial pink.

Opposite him is the only man who clocks you, who is thin like verdaccio and hardly there at all.
(if: not ($haunts contains $haunt4))[Someone catches your eye.
<span class="guided-link">[[Approach him|The Stranger at the French]]</span>]
(if: ($haunts contains $haunt4) and not ($haunts contains $haunt1))[The drink has worked its way between your nerves. Though you might not entertain the artists, they might at least entertain you.
[[Approach the artists|Talk to the Artists]]]
(if: ($haunts contains $haunt1) and not ($haunts contains $haunt2))[In the corner, you spot a familiar face — a novelist now, though you knew him when he was a poet.
[[Approach him|Approach the novelist]]]
(if: ($haunts contains $haunt1) and ($haunts contains $haunt2))[You've done what you can here.
[[Leave the French|Dean Street]]
[[The Colony Room is just round the corner.|The Colony Room Door]]]
