:: The Interval {"position":"900,250","size":"100,100"}
(unless: $alba is an array)[(set: $alba to (a:))]
(unless: $haunts is an array)[(set: $haunts to (a:))]
(set: $visitedInterval to true)\
(set: $exploredSinceFrench to true)
You're descending a flight of stairs. The kind you find leaving a theatre; red carpet worn thin as your world in its dead middle.

A woman passes; she is going up. Two steps down you freeze like a broken clock, right twice a day: you'd know that perfume anywhere. It is Lily.
(set: $confidence to $confidence + 15)\
(set: $sobriety to $sobriety + 12)
(if: $haunts's length >= 7)[(if: not ($alba contains $alba3))[(set: $alba to $alba + (a: $alba3))

<div class="revelation-box">
<div class="revelation-header">⟡ ALBA ⟡</div>

She speaks, and the words are not hers:

<div class="alba-line">"$alba3"</div>

The scent of lily-of-the-valley.

She continues up the stairs. You continue down. But something has changed. The poem is complete.

<div class="revelation-footer">THE THIRD LINE — THE ALBA IS COMPLETE</div>
</div>]
(else:)['She lay beside me in the dawn.'

The scent of lily-of-the-valley.

She continues up the stairs. You continue down.]]
(else:)['She lay beside me in the dawn.'

The scent of lily-of-the-valley.

She continues up the stairs. You continue down.

<div class="blocked-message">
The words echo but do not settle. The night hasn't marked you enough. Go deeper.
</div>]

<span class="lily-thought">(link: "Turn — follow her")[You take the stairs by doubles but when you get there she's gone. Lily-of-the-Valley is all that remains; lingering a taunt, a haunt, another.]</span>

